		"description": "<p>At 11th level, as an action you can suggest an activity (limited to a sentence or two) to a creature that can hear and understand you. A creature that can&rsquo;t be charmed is immune to this feature. The course of action must sound reasonable, as with the @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-spells.Item.ml9ls27u9ncms8ko]{Suggestion} spell.</p>\n<p>If the target fails a Wisdom saving throw , it pursues the course of action you described to the best of its ability for as long as you are present, and for up to 10 minutes after.</p>\n<p>Once you use this feature, you must finish a short or long rest before you can use it again.</p>",
